SELF-DESCRIPTION: Liu Zhi & Fan Box

The three ends of the design: The designer, the customer, and the supplier are all affected

Coincidentally, several of the designers on our team were from Hubei Province. Fortunately, one of the designers had planned to return to Wuhan for the Spring Festival and temporarily changed his route to another city, Yichang. While most of the other members come from far and wide, it is difficult to go back to Beijing, even if they break through the blockade and return, but also need to be confined at home for 14 days. At the beginning of this year, most of our projects went into the detailed stage of brand maintenance, some even had to go to the scene. Designing this thing online is actually not enough communication. We tried the form of telecommuting and held several video conferences, more of a way for partners to meet in the clouds. In fact, there is no way to real-time feedback on the work, communication efficiency is relatively low, the main work is still done by colleagues in Beijing.

Pence visual system design

In fact, many times is not what we choose the industry's customers, but depends on what industry is more prosperous. Coincidentally, many of the projects we designed last year came from the catering industry, which has been hit hardest by the current economic downturn. In fact, we are particularly optimistic about the development of the catering industry in the coming years, until this outbreak. In the back we specially interviewed the "life and death only in the line between" a sit and forget. In addition, many of the clients we serve are doing crowd-sourcing projects. For example, exhibitions, large-scale events, in fact, the exhibition has been a relatively good momentum of development and more and more global industry, until this epidemic. Many projects have been delayed or cancelled. This year, there is an international film festival project. Now there are problems with exit and entry. The Film Festival itself is a gathering activity. Therefore, we are still waiting to see the policy and trend of the epidemic. It is a foregone conclusion to postpone the event. This year, another ABC Art Book Fair that we serve has been postponed, and posters and other promotional materials printed years ago have been scrapped. There are also events related to the Tokyo Olympics, where it has become normal for us to monitor the WHO's movements and news every day. The latest news is that the outbreak will be cancelled in May if it is not brought under control.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Some companies are also unable to change their visual image at this time. For example, years ago there was a customer, is the online dessert brand, find us want to do VI brand image upgrade. There was no time to chat before the festival. When I got in touch with him recently, the client said that he lost nearly one million yuan every month, and the raw materials needed to be imported could not come in. The employee's salary had to be paid as usual. "What we are thinking about now is how not to spend money.

The supplier is also a very important link in the design, the designer is only the design, the concrete realization of these designs or depends on the supplier. Now the printing presses won't start for at least three months, many southern suppliers are not expected to return to work, and some small factories are closing. The proofing of the 2020 year of the rat calendar we had planned to launch has been completed. Just waiting for the resin material to be imported, but after PHEIC, importing raw materials became extremely difficult, and the timeliness of the calendar as a carrier decided the end of this design direction, we will complete the design in a new form when the supplier returns to work.

This disaster has left a lot of people vulnerable

We are connected 24 / 7, but the feelings of anxiety, worry, frustration, and anger are at an all-time high, and they interact with the current environment, being caught up in the constant turbulence of the contradictions of reality.

There were nine people on our team. Unfortunately, one employee who had just come back to Beijing had a diagnosis in the next unit. Their community had also entered a particularly strict "wartime" management, they even had to prepare their own food for 14 days before the gate was sealed. Everyone has entered a stage of paranoia. Some people check various symptoms of infection to cope with their physical conditions. Others keep track of their body temperature every hour, one day even anxiety to 37.4 degrees... this is the reality of each of us, this disaster blew out a lot of people's vulnerability, when your inner world is not calm, in fact, can not do design-related things.

Design of vision system for original Wheat Hill

Now clients are more cautious and budgets will not be as generous, at least for the first half of the year, as they were before the outbreak. But in the long run, do not think the design industry will have a shuffle. Because the design profession has its particularity, the plane design studio mainly still looks at the main Creator's design logic and the ability. After a period of silence, the sequence will remain the same, but the industry that may be served will change.

The good thing is that we're leaving more time for our own design thinking, and there are probably a lot of projects that will take longer to Polish this year. For example, the festival was originally scheduled to be proposed in early February, and the postponement gives us more time to think about what kind of visual language is needed to balance the power aesthetic with that of the general public, and how to reverse the negative visual impact of previous film festivals in the mass media.

After the outbreak we will still be more of their own voice, combing the works of the past. We may not think about changing the scope of the business, but we think more about the "design" itself and the "people. ".

He who rules the world is a fool in times of trouble

Graphic design is the icing on the cake, and it does seem a bit useless to do it in the midst of an epidemic. The designer is "the ruler of the world, the bucket of troubled times" . In the world of design, the task is to ensure that the world is interesting and diverse, but in reverse, diversity is somewhat anachronistic.

In a relatively prosperous society, where there is a great demand for beauty and spirituality, our work is effective. Once we are transformed into an emergent society, will the aesthetic, the spiritual, the aesthetic, the lifestyle, continue to decline, and for how long, while people are busy satisfying the lowest of Maslow's needs, whether this exceptional state will become the norm and invade our daily lives is a question that worries us beyond just being a designer.

Remember, suffering is more important than cheering

After an outbreak, you think before you do anything: What's the point. We can't do anything that doesn't matter. Designers'greatest strength is to help people retain memories of this period of suffering after the epidemic has passed, rather than shouting slogans to cheer them on. We also received a commission to design a cheer poster for the plague, although the phrase "poetry after Auschwitz is shameful" was misappropriated by a certain anti-black, but in the midst of the plague poster design is absurd, not only is it not as good as the infographic design of the rescue message, it's not even as good as the first random donation to retweet, and it's an aesthetic and functional failure.

Self-description: Dong Mi

Emotions can be ups and downs

It was only later, almost on the 22nd, when it was time to stop work and go home for the Spring Festival, that it was widely reported that things had expanded faster than people expected. I wasn't sure what was going to happen, and I was still scared, so I packed up all my N95 masks and sent 40 to my parents'house before going home.

During holidays, I would do simple exercise in the morning, then read or write with a writing brush, and spend a long time making lunch, afternoons are spent watching movies or plays (eight Rohmer movies in a row, then "The Newsroom, " which is relevant to current events) . It used to be hard to stay at home all day and never get the hang of it, but now it's time to follow the path of the sun in your home and move between your bedroom and living room.

Open OBJECT on display in the PARK in Shanghai

About the epidemic is certainly concerned about progress, follow some analysis articles, to understand its source, infection process, symptoms, and so on; secondly, follow the Information Update of the Wuhan side of the medical sector, to see whether they are able to deal with a large number of patients; In the end, it is the repeated follow-up at these levels. Things change from day to day, and new problems and new solutions arise.

I have been getting information about this outbreak primarily from online sources, and I have personally experienced mood swings on several fronts, CONSTANTLY SWINGING BETWEEN DISAPPOINTMENT & HOPE, FEAR & confidence. The attitude at the beginning of the event may have been the same as most people, allowing themselves to be immersed in a flood of information and to be dominated by negative emotions. To some extent, it was as if I knew that both Wuhan and Hubei were suffering, and it would be inhuman for me to survive on my own, so you may also subconsciously choose to read more negative information.

But after a period of time, they find their emotions unbearable, so self-preservation mechanism activated, a controlled access to information every day. The fact that I'm going to be talking to a lot of my friends, exchanging ideas -- different people, different perspectives -- is interesting, and it gives me a new perspective on what's going on. Even friends of my own age and social background may have a different view of me, suggesting that each person's access to information may vary widely, in addition, everyone's information selection and processing mechanism is quite different, people's pursuit of truth is actually very difficult, complex information channels and ways of expression, eventually, it may be possible for people to still believe what they already believe. It is a suggestion I make to myself to admit the complexity of things, without too much ambition, to remain calm and to step back and observe.

Instead, the epidemic has made the job easier

After returning to work remotely, the hours are the same as before, and commutes are diverted to make lunch. I was a little anxious at first about working from home, and I felt out of control as I didn't see my colleagues. But so far, we've been back at work for almost three weeks, and we've grown accustomed to telecommuting, and we've found it to our advantage that, compared to a lot of face to face communication, the process of typing takes me away from the subject and communicates as an outsider, sometimes you see things more clearly.

The first aspect of the work is to find out whether the national policy has issued policy regulations favoring small and medium-sized enterprises; the second is the Regulations on the rework time in various places; the third is the Regulations on the isolation time for rework, etc. ; and the other is the degree of damage to the national economy, and predictions of a gradual recovery.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Moon White Bowl of OPEN OBJECT "half" series

Our studio has been working since February 3rd. Be prepared to go back to work from the start, asking employees to create a physical environment at home where they can work. On the first day we did a simple Pep talk to bring employees into our Big picture and encourage them to confidently embrace whatever comes next.

Fortunately, with the exception of the new model of working remotely, there isn't much impact. There are some more time-sensitive projects, because the outbreak of the relationship canceled. But the overall number of projects in the studio has not changed much. We've combed through our work again, trying to make it as if it weren't an outbreak, but it's something we're doing all the time, not an outbreak. The company-level adjustment on the epidemic, more in the psychological and conceptual adjustment. You can also click on the link Ways of Seeing to expand on this.

For Design companies, like everyone else in the epidemic, our clients face varying degrees of financial stress, which makes them more conscious of the balance of payments dimension when making decisions and adjustments. But maximizing results with a minimal budget has always been part of our philosophy, so for us, the goals are the same.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The OPEN OBJECT "line" series of flower vessels

For Brands, the upstream supply chain has pushed back production slightly because of the outbreak, but not to us. And for the downstream sales channels, because we have been in the layout of the line, combining online, b-end combined with c-end, the workload is very large, this period of time we just use to comb a lot of details of brand operations, to finalize cooperation, try to get the normal business activities back on track from March. There will be a few small stand-alone exhibitions scheduled for the first half to mid-, and at the current pace, they will be pushed back.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xu Zhi Exhibition

It's a good time to reflect

To be honest, my own profession as a designer doesn't play much of a role in the epidemic. I think all businesses can do is to reflect on the broader context of whether their previous business logic is correct, whether in the monist value system to continue to run forward without thinking. Now that the first quarter of 2020 is bound to be bad, the best we can do is to do our jobs and make up for lost time.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I'm sure many of us have had a conscious or forced pause to examine our work, during which time we felt we were communicating more deeply and understanding with our clients. We exchange ideas on a deeper level, have richer, more honest conversations about business models and business ideas, and have a feeling of working together as if I had never before, it's nice to feel that two individuals have some degree of personal humanity, that they understand each other and trust each other, and I think we'll want to keep that humanity in our future work with our clients.

Physical conditions shouldn't change much after the outbreak, and we won't be telecommuting for efficiency reasons. But after the outbreak, we are all "experienced" people, there must be some psychological growth, there will be more diverse perspectives to think and solve problems, more accustomed to asking a "why" , trying to get to the bottom of things, and that's what I'd like to see happen.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Every year in March, it is the Magnolia blossom season outside the window of our Sanlitun store. I hope this March we can still see the flowers bloom and fall as before, and I hope all of us can take off our masks and walk calmly down the street, it's free to breathe in the smell of spring. Thank you very much for the special period of media platform and Kol's help, hope the epidemic as soon as possible end, the brand safe and sound. Also hope that the partner can sit and forget to pass this special time, through this epidemic, can really grow up, really feel that each guest is hard-won and even valuable.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
ABC (Art Book in China) , an independent art book fair based in China, was banned from building a new visual system for its fifth anniversary.

Self: Zhao Mengsha

ABC: An apple a day, be a beginner again

Since last week, we have been informed of the cancellation of several major exhibitions in the art world. Also see to do the partner of the bookstore in succession in the life of crowdfunding. The impact of the epidemic is the entire industry, although the appearance of grief everywhere, but with the side of the "self-employed" friends to exchange, we are still calm, can not be considered "hang on. ". In the face of large-scale disasters, the advantages of individuals stand out, not dependent on self-sufficiency in capital units when it is easier to survive. We also have idealism, but more is the capacity to act.

The isolation time passed quickly, just as the usual busy book fair want to do not do things in this period of time to focus on doing. We've also made a new podcast called "Abecedarian for beginners" (apple / Himalaya / netease-yun can listen to it) , so feel free to take some action in response. After all, the whole point of doing ABC is to encourage everyone to start acting on their own.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
With the outbreak in doubt, ABC hopes to postpone the event

The first blow was the travel ban in the United States, which prevented us from attending the Metrial Art Book Fair in Mexico. The new magazine, which had been in the final stages years ago, was not ready for printing. The less optimistic part is the impact of the epidemic spreading overseas. Many countries have stopped granting visas to Chinese citizens. Several major airlines have extended their flights until the end of April, i don't think the La Abf Art Book Fair is GonNa Happen either.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Fifth ABC Art Book Fair in 2020 is currently scheduled to be postponed. Despite the uncertainties surrounding the development of the epidemic, the book fair is one of the rare opportunities to interact with our global counterparts each year, and we will not give up our annual expectations. We have also prepared a survey questionnaire for all past exhibitors and those who have applied, to find out what they really think and what they want, and to find out all the possibilities of solving the problem. We're not that pessimistic at the exhibition level, and things are moving forward as planned. After the disaster, we are eager to see old friends, need to get together and read, so no matter what time is postponed, I believe there will be exhibition and audience.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Hyde offers high quality print and derivative products for all walks of life, with a diverse mix of materials and processes. Qiliang Hyde was founded in 1995, from a second-hand four-open printing machine, customers all over the arts, manufacturing, books, education, finance, people's livelihood, exhibitions, government... in recent years to promote the research and development of cultural products, explore the possibilities of printing.

Self description: Zhou Shijun

Printing is an asset-heavy industry

Our company has a two-week holiday every Spring Festival. After all, it is a manufacturing enterprise. Employees are busy all the year round and need rest to adjust. Then the epidemic started... and there was no going back.

After and the company to explore various issues, understanding of Beijing and Shunyi district instructions, the resumption of work time pushed twice, is now scheduled to start on March 1.

The beginning is a little flustered, after the calm down, deep thinking about the work behind how to advance. Printing industry has a special feature, it is to serve the whole society, but also can reflect the economic development trend. A decade ago cars were a big part of Hyde's business, but with the development of smartphones, the car business has shrunk to only 2030% . On the other hand, the education industry has gained momentum, and headquarter companies are in great demand for printed materials. From the big trend, we do printing is "which pot to open, which pot to mention. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wulong Laoba international land art season peripheral materials produced by Qiliang Hyde Printing

Printing is a heavy asset industry, adding new equipment every year, high-end equipment is often one million. Paper and other major materials on the occupation of funds is also quite large. Personnel costs, because we have a large number of non-standard orders, with a lot of manual operators. Qiliang Hyde uses a one-to-one consulting model, dozens of sales teams to serve customers in various industries. Overall, our operating costs are quite high. The main task this year is to optimize the process, reduce costs, increase efficiency.

Crisis, crisis and opportunity

Since February 11, our sales team has been learning at home, reading material online before sharing it in large groups. There is also a daily discussion of sales skills, cross-functional collaboration, and so on, all the way to the start of the project. This is a good time to cut out distractions and improve yourself.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Full Monty Western brand packaging materials are printed by Qiliang Hyde

Some of our colleagues are more pessimistic, that the epidemic will severely hit the economy, do the industry's lack of funds, can be allocated to do printing even less. I am relatively optimistic, we are sailing against the current, to strengthen their ability to withstand pressure, once the general situation is better, there is certainly an opportunity.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
What the epidemic has brought to us is the reflection of individuals as well as society. In recent months, our values have been cycled through a series of collapses and reconstructions, and our work has been challenged as never before. But in any case, to find yourself in the dark, both to prepare for the worst, but also to keep in mind the obsession and hope.
